					<msContents class="lccn.loc.gov/n79053644" rend="visible">
						<summary>The Book of Esther. </summary>
						<textLang mainLang="he"/>
						<msItem rend="">
							<locus from="1r" to="2r"/>
							<title xml:lang="he-Latn-x-lc">Megilat Ester </title>
							<title xml:lang="he">מגלת אסתר</title>
							<note>
								<p>Some reading differ from the masoretic כתיב. </p>
							</note>
						</msItem>
					</msContents>
					<physDesc rend="visible">
						<p>Parchment scroll of the 17th century. </p>
						<objectDesc form="scroll ">
							<supportDesc material="perg">
								<support>Parchment. </support>
								<extent>11 membranes, 39 columns. <dimensions type="leaf" unit="mm">
										<height>95</height>
										<width>4354</width>
									</dimensions>
								</extent>
								<collation>
									<p>11 membranes, plus a detached leather strap. </p>
								</collation>
								<condition>
									<p>Excision at outermost end, and a sewn repair suggesting strap attached at some time and pulled away.
</p>
									<p>Damp darkening along edges, plus a few tidemarks. Few usage stains.</p>
									<p>Trimming has cut into edge. One small edge loss, and excessive trim in places.
</p>
								</condition>
							</supportDesc>
							<layoutDesc>
								<layout columns="39" ruledLines="11" writtenLines="11">
									<p>Uniform layout. </p>
									<p>Ruling by hard point,
membrane by membrane.</p>
									<p>Visible pricking. </p>
									<p>No tagin on שעטנזגץ, and one on the letter ח of חור, 1:6. Minuscular letters entirely absent. </p>
									<p>The names of the sons of Haman arranged in 11 lines, in accordance with the rule. </p>
									<p>Sections 6:1 and 7:5 open. </p>
									<p>Some erasures. </p>
								</layout>
							</layoutDesc>
						</objectDesc>
						<handDesc hands="1">
							<summary>Sefardi square script of the 17th century.</summary>
							<handNote script="Hebrew" scope="sole"/>
						</handDesc>
						<additions>
							<p>A mezuzah, or door-phylactery, attached to the roll at the end (an extra membrane of 70 x 95mm attached at the inner end).</p>
